Items.vs: Detroit Pistons vs. New Jersey Nets

Items.description: Miami extended its home win streak to 16 by beating the Hornets 85-77 to advance to the East semis.
Items.vs: Miami Heat vs. New Orleans Hornets

Items.description: Mike Bibby scored 33 points for the Kings in a 104-98 victory over the top-seeded Timberwolves on Tuesday night.
Tony Parker scored eight of his 30 points in the fourth quarter, including a stunning crossover that fooled Devean George and ended the Lakers' final push.
Items.vs: San Antonio Spurs vs. Los Angeles Lakers

Items.description: An 11-day layoff didn't make the Pacers too rusty, as they dominated the weary Miami Heat in Game 1 of their Eastern semifinal Thursday night.
The Nets raced to a 12-point halftime lead in Game 2 only to see Detroit finish them off 95-80, the Pistons' sixth double-digit win of the playoffs.
Items.vs: Detroit Pistons vs. New Jersey Nets

Items.description: Miami got off to a solid start in Game 2, but Reggie Miller's buzzer-beating 3 to end the first half jump-started the Pacers' dominance thereafter.
Sam Cassell scored eight points in the final three minutes, and the Timberwolves closed out Game 2 with a 16-1 run and evened the series.
Home cooking appeared to be the remedy for the Los Angeles Lakers, who clamped down on Tony Parker and the Spurs in Game 3.
Items.vs: Los Angeles Lakers vs. San Antonio Spurs

Items.description: Richard Jefferson had a career playoff-high 30 points as the Nets finally put together 48 minutes of decent basketball to put away the Pistons in Game 3.
Items.vs: New Jersey Nets vs. Detroit Pistons

Items.description:
Dwyane Wade scored 14 of his 25 points in the fourth
quarter, and the Heat handed the visiting Pacers their first loss of the postseason.
With several clutch baskets, Kevin Garnett (30 points, 15 rebounds) saved Minnesota from a disheartening loss and reclaimed home-court advantage.
Jason Kidd's 7th career postseason triple-double sparked a big win for New Jersey. With the series tied, it's the Pistons' turn to defend their turf Friday.
Items.vs: New Jersey Nets vs. Detroit Pistons

Items.description: After spending much of Tuesday in a Colorado courtroom, Kobe Bryant scored 42 points in L.A.'s Game 4 victory that evened the series.
Items.vs: Los Angeles Lakers vs. San Antonio Spurs

Items.description: Lamar Odom scored 22 points and Caron Butler added 21 to lead the Heat to a 100-88 victory over the Pacers on Wednesday in Miami. The series is tied 2-2.
Chris Webber scored a playoff-high 28 points and Brad Miller added 20 to lead the Kings to an 87-81 victory over the Timberwolves on Wednesday night in Game 4.
Two unbelievable last-second shots. Tim Duncan's saved the Spurs a home loss. But, then, Derek Fisher's gave the Lakers the win and the series lead.
Items.vs: San Antonio Spurs vs. Los Angeles Lakers

Items.description: The Nets'  Richard Jefferson emerged to score 18 of his 31 after regulation, leading N.J. to a huge road win after four hours and three OTs Friday.
Items.vs: Detroit Pistons vs. New Jersey Nets

Items.description: Latrell Sprewell and the Timberwolves did their part in defending home turf Friday. Now it's Sacramento's turn in Game 6 on Sunday.
Jeff Foster's career highs of 20 points and 16 boards sparked Indiana's win, giving them a 3-2 edge. The Heat will look to respond in Miami on Tuesday.

The Lakers completed an improbable comeback Saturday night, sending the defending NBA champion San Antonio
Spurs home for the summer.
Items.vs: Los Angeles Lakers vs. San Antonio Spurs

Items.description: The energetic Kings used made good on Chris Webber's guarantee by routing the Wolves at Arco. Game 7 is Wednesday at Target Center.
Rip Hamilton's 24 points and Ben Wallace's 20 rebounds fueled the Pistons' road victory Sunday. The series will be settled Thursday in Detroit.
Items.vs: New Jersey Nets vs. Detroit Pistons

Items.description: Indiana got 27 points from Ron Artest and withstood Dwyane Wade's fourth-quarter burst in dealing Miami a rare home loss to reach the East finals.
Kevin Garnett had 32 points, 21 rebounds and five blocks on his 28th birthday, and the Wolves held on to top the Kings 83-80 in Game 7 Wednesday night.
The Pistons' blowout win in the decisive Game 7 Thursday night ended New Jersey's two-year reign as the Eastern Conference champions.
Items.vs: Detroit Pistons vs. New Jersey Nets

Items.description: With five days off and a well-rested Shaq, the Lakers wasted no time prying the home-court edge from the Wolves.
Items.vs: Minnesota Timberwolves vs. Los Angeles Lakers

Items.description: After missing his first six shots, Reggie Miller drilled a 3-pointer with 31.7 seconds left to put Indiana ahead to stay at Conseco.
No Sam I Am? No problem, as Latrell Sprewell (17 points), Wally Szczerbiak (16) and Darrick Martin (15) helped Minnesota avoid an 0-2 hole.
Items.vs: Minnesota Timberwolves vs. Los Angeles Lakers

Items.description: Tayshaun Prince sprinted downcourt to block a breakaway game-tying layup by Reggie Miller, and Detroit held on to gain a split at Conseco.
Shaquille O'Neal and Kobe Bryant scored 22 points each and the Lakers took a 2-1 edge over the Wolves in the Western Conference finals.
Items.vs: Los Angeles Lakers vs. Minnesota Timberwolves

Items.description: Rasheed Wallace made another loud statement, only this time he did it during the Pistons' 85-78 win instead of before the game or after it.
Returning to L.A. less than two hours before tipoff, Kobe Bryant scored 31 points and led the Lakers to a  Game 4 win in the Western Conference finals.
Items.vs: Los Angeles Lakers vs. Minnesota Timberwolves

Items.description: Austin Croshere made his first start in more than two years and scored 14 points Friday night, providing Indiana with a much-needed offensive option in an 83-68 victory.
With Sam Cassell out, Kevin Garnett (30 points) and Latrell Sprewell (28) helped the Wolves avoid elimination Saturday and send the series back to L.A.
Items.vs: Minnesota Timberwolves vs. Los Angeles Lakers

Items.description: Dubbed "Mini-Me" by Reggie Miller, Richard Hamilton scored 33 points to lead the Pistons to within one victory of the NBA Finals.
Shaquille O'Neal had 25 points and 11 rebounds, and Kareem Rush hit six 3-pointers in Los Angeles' 96-90 victory over the Timberwolves on Monday.
Items.vs: Los Angeles Lakers vs. Minnesota Timberwolves

Items.description: In one of the lowest-scoring games in NBA playoff history, Richard Hamilton put the Pistons up for good late in the fourth quarter of their 69-65 Game 6 win.

Controlling the tempo, uglifying the game and stunning a
star-studded crowd, the Pistons pulled off a shocker in Los Angeles on Sunday night.
Items.vs: Los Angeles Lakers vs. Detroit Pistons

Items.description: Kobe Bryant came through in the clutch, saving the Lakers in regulation and carrying them in overtime. He buried a tying 3 with 2.1 seconds left, then dominated.
Items.vs: Los Angeles Lakers vs. Detroit Pistons

Items.description: Hustling 36-year-old Elden Campbell's breakaway dunk symbolized the entire night in Detroit's 88-68 victory over Los Angeles in Game 3.
Items.vs: Detroit Pistons vs. Los Angeles Lakers

Items.description: Building a lead early in the final period, holding it and repelling every Lakers rally, Detroit moved one win closer to its first title in 14 years.
Items.vs: Detroit Pistons vs. Los Angeles Lakers

Items.description: Detroit humiliated  the Lakers at the Palace on Tuesday night for its first title since 1990. Chauncey Billups was named Finals MVP.
Items.vs: Detroit Pistons vs. Los Angeles Lakers
